He's the determined young koala who survived an 80km ride clinging to the front grille of a car in Queensland - and remarkably escaped with just a bruised nose and scratch toe nail.

The four-year-old koala was hit on Thursday around Marborough, north of the Sunshine Coast, and was spotted still hanging onto the car when it pulled into a service station at Gypmie 88km away. 

A taxi driver took the 5.75kg koala from the driver of the car and drove him to a nearby vet clinic, before he was taken to Australia Zoo on Friday to be treated.

