Dr Millers said the koala had been named 'Timber Wolf' because he was brought to the zoo by the men who collect leaves for the animals.

She said the furry marsupial would have been hit while he was searching for a mate.

The zoo treats about 900 koalas each year and most of them injure themselves between July and December when they're on the move searching for a mate during the breeding season.

