'He’s recovering well but we need to know where to return him. He's very lucky to be alive,' Dr Millers said. 

The zoo want to track down the driver to work out where the koala was hit in a bid to return him to the correct area on the Sunshine Coast.

'Koalas are territorial animals so he needs to go back to where he's come from,' Dr Millers said.

 

